;; Root.synth — synth surface (v0.20)
;;
;; A synth file is a sequence of rules. Each rule is either
;; Sequential (bare items on a line) or OrderedChoice (// lines).
;;
;; This surface is self-description for tooling (editors,
;; linters, documentation). askicc uses its own hand-written
;; parser to bootstrap — this dialect data is NOT what askicc
;; uses to parse .synth files.

*<SynthRule>
